            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I really enjoy the fact that checkhealth prints to stdout, it meshes super well with GitHub CI runners. If there was some separate structured `vim.health.<something>()` API, I'm guessing I'd be on the hook for formatting and printing it. Why do all that when there's a simpler alternative.\n\nAs far as I know I'm probably the only person who tried to use checkhealth's API for anything non-trivial. At least [a quick search in all of GitHub](https://github.com/search?q=vim.cmd.checkhealth+path%3A**%2F*.lua&type=code&p=1) shows that it's only used in 40 lua files. Who would be disrupted by changing the names?",
